# Sharpee Grammar Design

## Analysis of Inform 10's Approach

Looking at Inform 10's grammar, we can identify several key patterns:

### 1. Command Aliases
```
Understand the commands "carry" and "hold" as "take".
```
This maps synonyms to a canonical action. We should handle this in our pattern syntax.

### 2. Object Preferences
```
Understand "drop [things preferably held]" as dropping.
```
The "preferably held" hint helps disambiguation. We could use scope hints.

### 3. Directional Variants
```
Understand "get in/on" as entering.
Understand "get out/off/down/up" as exiting.
```
Multiple prepositions map to the same action based on context.

### 4. Reversed Noun Order
```
Understand "give [someone] [something preferably held]" as giving it to (with nouns reversed).
```
Flexible word order for natural language.

### 5. Multi-word Verbs
```
Understand "pick up [things]" or "pick [things] up" as taking.
```
Phrasal verbs with flexible positioning.

## Sharpee's Grammar Categories

### 1. Object Manipulation
**Core actions that interact with things**

```typescript
// Taking variants
{ pattern: 'take|get|pick up|grab|carry|hold <noun>', action: 'taking' }
{ pattern: 'pick <noun> up', action: 'taking' }
{ pattern: 'take <noun> from|off <second>', action: 'removing' }

// Dropping variants  
{ pattern: 'drop|put down|discard|throw <noun>', action: 'dropping' }
{ pattern: 'put <noun> down', action: 'dropping' }

// Inserting (containers)
{ pattern: 'put|place|insert <noun> in|into|inside <second>', action: 'inserting' }
{ pattern: 'drop <noun> in|into|down <second>', action: 'inserting' }

// Putting (supporters)
{ pattern: 'put|place <noun> on|onto <second>', action: 'putting on' }
{ pattern: 'drop <noun> on|onto <second>', action: 'putting on' }

// Removing from containers/supporters
{ pattern: 'remove|take|get <noun> from|off <second>', action: 'removing' }
```

### 2. Movement & Position
**Getting around and changing position**

```typescript
// Basic movement
{ pattern: 'go|walk|run|move <direction>', action: 'going' }
{ pattern: '<direction>', action: 'going' }  // Just "north" or "n"

// Entering/Exiting
{ pattern: 'enter|go into|go in|get in|get into <noun>', action: 'entering' }
{ pattern: 'exit|leave|go out|get out|get off', action: 'exiting' }
{ pattern: 'get out of|get off <noun>', action: 'getting off' }

// Climbing
{ pattern: 'climb|climb up|climb over|scale <noun>', action: 'climbing' }

// Standing/Sitting
{ pattern: 'stand|stand up', action: 'exiting' }  // Context: when sitting
{ pattern: 'sit on|sit in|sit down on <noun>', action: 'entering' }
```

### 3. Examination & Senses
**Looking at and sensing things**

```typescript
// Looking
{ pattern: 'look|l', action: 'looking' }
{ pattern: 'look at|look|examine|x|watch|check <noun>', action: 'examining' }
{ pattern: 'look in|look inside|look into|search <noun>', action: 'searching' }
{ pattern: 'look under <noun>', action: 'looking under' }

// Reading
{ pattern: 'read <noun>', action: 'examining' }  // For readable things
{ pattern: 'read about <topic> in <noun>', action: 'consulting' }

// Other senses
{ pattern: 'smell|sniff <noun>', action: 'smelling' }
{ pattern: 'taste <noun>', action: 'tasting' }
{ pattern: 'touch|feel <noun>', action: 'touching' }
{ pattern: 'listen|listen to|hear <noun>', action: 'listening' }
```

### 4. Conversation
**Talking to NPCs**

```typescript
// Direct conversation
{ pattern: 'ask <noun> about <topic>', action: 'asking about' }
{ pattern: 'tell <noun> about <topic>', action: 'telling about' }
{ pattern: 'ask <noun> for <second>', action: 'asking for' }

// Speech
{ pattern: 'say|answer|shout|speak <text> to <noun>', action: 'answering' }
{ pattern: 'answer <text>', action: 'saying' }  // Context-dependent

// Social actions
{ pattern: 'give|offer|pay|feed <noun> to <second>', action: 'giving' }
{ pattern: 'give <second> <noun>', action: 'giving', reversed: true }
{ pattern: 'show|present|display <noun> to <second>', action: 'showing' }
{ pattern: 'show <second> <noun>', action: 'showing', reversed: true }
```

### 5. Manipulation & Tools
**Using objects and tools**

```typescript
// Opening/Closing
{ pattern: 'open|unwrap|uncover <noun>', action: 'opening' }
{ pattern: 'open <noun> with <second>', action: 'unlocking' }
{ pattern: 'close|shut|cover <noun>', action: 'closing' }

// Locking/Unlocking  
{ pattern: 'lock <noun> with <second>', action: 'locking' }
{ pattern: 'unlock <noun> with <second>', action: 'unlocking' }

// Switching
{ pattern: 'turn on|switch on|activate <noun>', action: 'switching on' }
{ pattern: 'turn <noun> on', action: 'switching on' }
{ pattern: 'turn off|switch off|deactivate <noun>', action: 'switching off' }
{ pattern: 'turn <noun> off', action: 'switching off' }

// Physical manipulation
{ pattern: 'turn|rotate|twist|screw|unscrew <noun>', action: 'turning' }
{ pattern: 'push|move|shift|press <noun>', action: 'pushing' }
{ pattern: 'push <noun> <direction>', action: 'pushing to' }
{ pattern: 'pull|drag <noun>', action: 'pulling' }
```

### 6. Clothing
**Wearing and removing clothing**

```typescript
{ pattern: 'wear|put on|don <noun>', action: 'wearing' }
{ pattern: 'put <noun> on', action: 'wearing' }
{ pattern: 'take off|remove|shed|doff|disrobe <noun>', action: 'taking off' }
{ pattern: 'take <noun> off', action: 'taking off' }
```

### 7. Consumption & Body
**Eating, drinking, and bodily actions**

```typescript
{ pattern: 'eat|consume <noun>', action: 'eating' }
{ pattern: 'drink|sip|swallow <noun>', action: 'drinking' }
{ pattern: 'sleep|nap', action: 'sleeping' }
{ pattern: 'wake|wake up|awake|awaken', action: 'waking up' }
{ pattern: 'wake|wake up <noun>', action: 'waking' }
```

### 8. Violence & Destruction
**Aggressive actions**

```typescript
{ pattern: 'attack|hit|fight|punch|kick|strike <noun>', action: 'attacking' }
{ pattern: 'break|smash|destroy|wreck|crack <noun>', action: 'attacking' }
{ pattern: 'kill|murder <noun>', action: 'attacking' }  // Extreme violence
{ pattern: 'cut|slice|chop <noun>', action: 'cutting' }
{ pattern: 'burn|light <noun>', action: 'burning' }
{ pattern: 'throw|hurl <noun> at <second>', action: 'throwing at' }
```

### 9. Social & Emotional
**Non-violent interpersonal actions**

```typescript
{ pattern: 'kiss|hug|embrace <noun>', action: 'kissing' }
{ pattern: 'wave', action: 'waving hands' }
{ pattern: 'wave <noun>', action: 'waving' }
{ pattern: 'think', action: 'thinking' }
{ pattern: 'wait|z', action: 'waiting' }
```

### 10. Meta Commands
**Game control and information**

```typescript
{ pattern: 'inventory|inv|i', action: 'taking inventory' }
{ pattern: 'look|l', action: 'looking' }
{ pattern: 'score', action: 'requesting score' }
{ pattern: 'save', action: 'saving' }
{ pattern: 'restore|load', action: 'restoring' }
{ pattern: 'restart', action: 'restarting' }
{ pattern: 'quit|q', action: 'quitting' }
{ pattern: 'undo', action: 'undoing' }
{ pattern: 'again|g', action: 'repeating' }
```

## Design Principles for Sharpee

### 1. Canonical Actions
Each action has ONE canonical name (e.g., 'taking') with all synonyms in the pattern.

### 2. Scope Hints
Instead of "preferably held", we use our scoring system:
- Items in inventory get bonus points
- Visible items score higher than known items
- Recently mentioned items score highest

### 3. Flexible Prepositions
List all common prepositions in patterns:
```typescript
prepositions: ['in', 'into', 'inside']  // All mean the same
```

### 4. Reversed Patterns
Instead of a special syntax, just add both patterns:
```typescript
{ pattern: 'give <noun> to <second>', action: 'giving' }
{ pattern: 'give <second> <noun>', action: 'giving', reversed: true }
```

### 5. Contextual Actions
Some patterns depend on context:
- "stand" ‚Üí 'exiting' when sitting
- "get down" ‚Üí 'exiting' when on something
- "enter" ‚Üí 'going' to an adjacent room

### 6. Multi-word Handling
Support both forms of phrasal verbs:
```typescript
{ pattern: 'pick up <noun>', action: 'taking' }
{ pattern: 'pick <noun> up', action: 'taking' }
```

## Implementation Strategy

### Phase 1: Core Actions
Start with the most common actions:
- taking, dropping, examining, going
- opening, closing, entering, exiting
- giving, showing, asking, telling

### Phase 2: Extended Actions  
Add less common but important actions:
- wearing, taking off
- locking, unlocking
- switching on/off
- pushing, pulling

### Phase 3: Special Actions
Add actions that need special handling:
- consulting (needs text parsing)
- pushing to direction
- throwing at
- setting to

### Phase 4: Meta Commands
Game control that bypasses normal action processing:
- save, restore, quit
- undo, again
- score, inventory

## Pattern Syntax Extensions

We might want to add:

### 1. Optional Words
```typescript
pattern: 'look (at) <noun>'  // "look door" or "look at door"
```

### 2. Multiple Objects
```typescript
pattern: 'take <noun+>'  // "take key and lamp"
```

### 3. Except Clauses
```typescript
pattern: 'take all (except|but) <noun>'
```

### 4. Number Support
```typescript
pattern: 'take <number> <noun>'  // "take 3 coins"
```

## Localization Considerations

Each language needs:
1. Translated patterns
2. Language-specific prepositions
3. Cultural action variants
4. Appropriate abbreviations

Spanish example:
```typescript
{ pattern: 'tomar|coger|agarrar <noun>', action: 'taking' }
{ pattern: 'n|norte', action: 'going' }  // Spanish abbreviations
```

# Sharpee Grammar Implementation Plan

## Core Design Decisions

1. **Action Categorization** - Grammar organized by action categories
2. **Inline Synonyms** - All synonyms in the pattern string
3. **Scope Hints** - Patterns can specify preferred object scope
4. **Compound Commands** - Support for "all", "and", "except" constructs
5. **Implicit Actions** - Only for directions and explicit action words
6. **Error Handling** - Via event system, with exceptions for disambiguation

## Enhanced Pattern Syntax

### Scope Hints
```typescript
<noun>           // Any object in scope
<noun:held>      // Prefer items in inventory
<noun:here>      // Prefer items in current location
<noun:worn>      // Prefer worn items
<noun:container> // Prefer containers
<noun:person>    // Prefer people/NPCs
```

### Compound Patterns
```typescript
<noun+>          // One or more objects: "take key and lamp"
<noun*>          // Zero or more objects: "drop all"
all|everything   // Special keyword for all applicable objects
all|everything (except|but) <noun+>  // Exclusion lists
```

### Optional Words
```typescript
(at)             // Optional word: "look (at) <noun>"
```

## Grammar Categories

### 1. Object Manipulation

```typescript
// Taking - the most fundamental action
{
  id: 'taking',
  pattern: 'take|get|pick up|grab|carry|hold <noun+:here>',
  action: 'taking',
  iterateObjects: true  // Apply to each object in noun+
}

// Alternative phrasal verb form
{
  id: 'taking-phrasal',
  pattern: 'pick <noun+:here> up',
  action: 'taking',
  iterateObjects: true
}

// Take all
{
  id: 'taking-all',
  pattern: 'take|get all|everything',
  action: 'taking',
  matchAll: true,
  scopeFilter: 'takeable'  // Only takeable items
}

// Take all except
{
  id: 'taking-all-except',
  pattern: 'take|get all|everything (except|but) <noun+>',
  action: 'taking',
  matchAll: true,
  except: true,
  scopeFilter: 'takeable'
}

// Taking from containers
{
  id: 'removing',
  pattern: 'take|get|remove <noun+> from|off <second:container>',
  action: 'removing',
  requiresSecond: true,
  iterateObjects: true
}

// Dropping
{
  id: 'dropping',
  pattern: 'drop|put down|discard|throw <noun+:held>',
  action: 'dropping',
  iterateObjects: true
}

// Dropping with phrasal verb
{
  id: 'dropping-phrasal',
  pattern: 'put <noun+:held> down',
  action: 'dropping',
  iterateObjects: true
}

// Inserting into containers
{
  id: 'inserting',
  pattern: 'put|place|insert <noun+:held> in|into|inside <second:container>',
  action: 'inserting',
  requiresSecond: true,
  prepositions: ['in', 'into', 'inside'],
  iterateObjects: true
}

// Putting on supporters
{
  id: 'putting-on',
  pattern: 'put|place <noun+:held> on|onto <second:supporter>',
  action: 'putting on',
  requiresSecond: true,
  prepositions: ['on', 'onto'],
  iterateObjects: true
}
```

### 2. Movement & Navigation

```typescript
// Basic movement
{
  id: 'going',
  pattern: 'go|walk|run|move <direction>',
  action: 'going'
}

// Implicit go for directions
{
  id: 'going-implicit',
  pattern: '<direction>',
  action: 'going'
}

// Entering objects/locations
{
  id: 'entering',
  pattern: 'enter|go (in|into)|get (in|into) <noun:enterable>',
  action: 'entering'
}

// Exiting current location/container
{
  id: 'exiting',
  pattern: 'exit|leave|go out|get (out|off)',
  action: 'exiting'
}

// Getting off specific things
{
  id: 'getting-off',
  pattern: 'get (off|out of)|exit <noun:here>',
  action: 'getting off'
}

// Climbing
{
  id: 'climbing',
  pattern: 'climb (up|over)|scale <noun:here>',
  action: 'climbing'
}
```

### 3. Examination & Senses

```typescript
// Looking around
{
  id: 'looking',
  pattern: 'look|l',
  action: 'looking'
}

// Examining objects
{
  id: 'examining',
  pattern: 'look (at)|examine|x|watch|check|inspect <noun>',
  action: 'examining'
}

// Searching inside things
{
  id: 'searching',
  pattern: 'look (in|inside|into)|search <noun:container>',
  action: 'searching'
}

// Looking under
{
  id: 'looking-under',
  pattern: 'look under|beneath <noun:here>',
  action: 'looking under'
}

// Reading
{
  id: 'reading',
  pattern: 'read <noun:readable>',
  action: 'examining'  // Just examining with special text
}

// Consulting
{
  id: 'consulting',
  pattern: 'look up|consult|read about <topic> in <noun:readable>',
  action: 'consulting',
  requiresSecond: true,
  textCapture: 'topic'
}
```

### 4. Conversation

```typescript
// Asking about topics
